'''Jorallan opal''' was a type of exquisite [[Opal/Legends|opal]] [[Gemstone/Legends|gemstone]] that could be found on<ref name="CSWE Jorallan" /> the terrestrial<ref name="TSWPC">''[[The Star Wars Planets Collection]]''</ref> [[Mid Rim/Legends|Mid Rim]]<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}} &mdash; Based on corresponding data for [[Joralla system/Legends|Joralla system]]</ref> [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Joralla]].<ref name="TSWPC" /> Jorallan opals were worth from two to twenty thousand [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] per [[Coruscant Standard Carat]] and were among the types of plunder favored by [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]].<ref name="Pirates" /> By approximately [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]],<ref name="Date">{{FarOrbitDate}}</ref> the cargo of the [[Star Galleon-class frigate|''Star Galleon''-class frigate]] [[Emperor's Will (Star Galleon-class)|''Emperor's Will'']], a [[treasure ship]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], included a [[Mythra/Legends|mythra]]-chain [[Necklace/Legends|necklace]] of twelve Jorallan opals, thirty-six carats in total.<ref name="GrandPrize" />

{{RPG|"[[The Grand Prize]]"}}
Around that [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="Date" /> the crew of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] [[Privateer/Legends|privateer]] [[EF76 Nebulon-B escort frigate/Legends|frigate]]<ref name="FarOrbit">''[[The Far Orbit Project]]''</ref> ''[[Far Orbit]]'' [[Capture of the Emperor's Will|captured]] the cargo of the ''Emperor's Will'', including the Jorallan opal necklace.<ref name="GrandPrize" />
{{Endgame}}

==Behind the scenes==
Jorallan opals were first mentioned in [[Timothy S. O'Brien]]'s [[1997]] [[West End Games]]' ''[[Star Wars: The Roleplaying Game]]'' sourcebook ''[[Pirates & Privateers]]''.<ref name="Pirates" /> They then went on to have their first full appearance in "[[The Grand Prize]]," a [[Roleplaying game|roleplaying]] adventure authored by O'Brien and included in the [[1998]] book ''[[The Far Orbit Project]]''.<ref name="GrandPrize" />

